# Cursor Rules for Configs Workspace

## Package Manager
- Always use `pnpm` instead of `npm` for package management
- Use `pnpm install` instead of `npm install`
- Use `pnpm add` instead of `npm install <package>`
- Use `pnpm remove` instead of `npm uninstall <package>`
- Use `pnpm update` instead of `npm update`
- Use `pnpm outdated` instead of `npm outdated`

## Workspace Management
- This is a pnpm workspace with multiple packages
- Use `pnpm -w` for workspace-level commands
- Use `pnpm --filter <package-name>` for package-specific commands
- Always run commands from the appropriate directory or use workspace filters

## Code Style
- Follow the existing ESLint and Prettier configurations
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Maintain consistent formatting and linting rules across all packages
